THE KINDNESS CHALLENGE PROJECT:

This weekend, I sat in church as a guest speaker spoke on the topic of really understanding how to be INENTIONAL in being KIND to others daily. Kind to others? 
I bet you’re probably saying the same thing I did. “But I think I’m already a pretty kind person?” I know right. I said the EXACT same thing. Then I got to thinking about how my actions each day really affect my mood and how I respond to things or people can sometimes determine if I have a GOOD or BAD day. 
Then she said this…”Whether or not we THRIVE IN LIFE, is far more dependent on how WE TREAT PEOPLE and not so much HOW PEOPLE TREAT US.” #YES It’s SO true. 
Our lives, whether in personal or business relationships depend greatly on how we TREAT OTHERS. I originally wanted to open this challenge up to my team of coaches only, because in our area of business we engage with others DAILY and its our FOCUS to help bring results to those who trust in us and create relationships far deeper than just choosing a workout program and meal plan that suites them. I take what I do seriously and I love engaging with people daily and the more I thought about this challenge, the more I thought SO MANY could benefit from something like this.

WHAT’S THE CHALLENGE YOU SAY? 
Today we were challenged to spend 30 DAYS choosing 1-2 people who we would INTENTIONALLY change our actions, thoughts, responses to…You’ll think about people in your life that maybe you feel like you have a tendency to have a hard time with some days, or people who seem to mentally drain you, maybe you have some ENERGY VAMPIRES in your life who you want to think about specifically. These can be family members, friends, work relationships, your spouse, etc. We are going to focus on changing our REACTIONS to things and how we respond in hopes that we can not only REALLY CHANGE things for the positive in their lives, but also ENRICH OUR OWN. 
So often I let my frustrations come out in the form of body language, a change in my voice and tone, sarcasm, exasperation, venting…And what I’m quickly learning is that ALL OF THAT affects our relationships and how we view LIFE in general. {more in comments}
